OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1784701089
OL,3,CRussian warship conducted weapon
OL,4,Cfiring exercise off the coast of
OL,5,CPlymouth
OL,7,FA Russian warship carried out a live-
OL,8,Ffire training exercise off the coast
OL,9,Fof Plymouth on Monday, the Ministry of
OL,10,FDefence (MoD) has confirmed.
OL,12,FThe Royal Navy monitored the
OL,13,FNeustrashimy as it fired for 30
OL,14,Fminutes, approximately 40 nautical
OL,15,Fmiles south of the Devon city.
OL,17,FThe Russian warship told the HMS Tyne
OL,18,Fit was planning to fire and asked the
OL,19,Fship to move to a safer distance
OL,20,Fbefore the exercise began.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/5
